705667f-b.text:
Meeker Avenue, east from Humboldt Street, showing the thorough-fare after it was widened as an approach to the Kosciusco Bridge.
Numerous buildings were dozed.
View 2 is from North Henry 'Street, and view 3 at Kingsland Avenue.
Note the Ehnickerbocker Ice plant.
P. L. Eperr  September 1, 1939
NO REPRODUCTIONS  Views 1-3
